⭐ Overview of Laravel Framework and Its Features
🔷 What is Laravel?

Laravel is a free, open-source PHP web framework used for developing modern web applications.

It follows the MVC (Model–View–Controller) architecture and helps developers build applications faster with clean and structured code.

👉 Created by: Taylor Otwell

🔷 Overview of Laravel Framework

Laravel provides a structured way to develop web applications by offering built-in tools and features like routing, authentication, database management, and templating.

It simplifies complex tasks such as:

Database operations
User authentication
Session handling
API development
🔷 Features of Laravel
1. MVC Architecture
Laravel follows Model–View–Controller pattern
Helps in separating logic, UI, and data
2. Routing System
Simple and powerful routing mechanism
Maps URLs to specific functions
3. Eloquent ORM (Object Relational Mapping)
Easy database handling using PHP syntax instead of SQL
Each table is represented as a model
4. Blade Template Engine
Lightweight templating engine
Supports dynamic content with simple syntax
5. Built-in Authentication
Ready-made system for:
Login
Registration
Password reset
6. Security Features

Laravel protects against:

SQL Injection
Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)
7. Artisan CLI (Command Line Tool)
Helps to automate tasks like:
Creating controllers
Running migrations
Starting server
8. Database Migration & Seeding
Migrations allow version control of database
Seeding helps insert sample data easily
9. Session & Cache Management
Handles user sessions efficiently
Supports caching for better performance
10. API Development Support
Easily build RESTful APIs
Useful for mobile and web apps
🔷 Advantages of Laravel
Easy to learn
Clean and readable code
Saves development time
Strong community support
Highly secure
